article.headline: Jackrabbits jump out to 10-0 lead, then go on 15-0 run to finish IUPUI
article.linkText: Pair of bursts fuel No. 23 South Dakota State
article.story:
BROOKINGS, S.D. -- Jill Young scored 17 points and Ketty Cornemann added 15 to lead No. 23 South Dakota State to a 96-49 victory over IUPUI on Saturday night.

Kristin Rotert had 12 points and Jennifer Warkenthien 11 for the Jackrabbits (15-2, 4-1 Summit), who hit 11 3-pointers.

South Dakota State dominated the entire game taking a 45-19 lead at the half.

Julia Whitted led the Jaguars (7-8, 2-2) with 14 points and 11 rebounds for a double-double. Nicole James added 11 points. IUPUI committed 27 turnovers.
